The paper deals with the problem of person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves meta-learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves attention-based architectures, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.NE.
